# CODEOWNERS
#
# This file establishes ownership for two surfaces:
#
#   1. `.review/**` — Tier 3 artifact handoff payloads per ADR-0006 / ADR-0007.
#      Belt-and-suspenders for the `.github/workflows/artifact-review-guard.yml`
#      label-gated merge guard: even if a future change weakens that workflow,
#      CODEOWNERS review on `.review/**` provides a second policy surface.
#
#   2. `agent/vendor/pi/{VERSION,CHECKSUMS}` — the pi runtime trust pin per
#      ADR-0009. A malicious bump landing a forged digest + matching forged
#      release tag would defeat `fetch_pi_binary()`'s checksum gate. Requiring
#      named-reviewer approval on every bump PR closes that path. The same
#      logic applies to `agent/vendor/nvm/{VERSION,CHECKSUMS}` per ADR-0010
#      — the nvm installer trust root sha256-gates a curl-to-bash, so a
#      malicious bump would defeat ih_ensure_nvm's verify-then-execute order.
#      Extended to `agent/vendor/{gh,yq,shellcheck}/{VERSION,CHECKSUMS}` per
#      ADR-0011 and `agent/vendor/gitleaks/{VERSION,CHECKSUMS}` per ADR-0037
#      — each is a separate sha256-pinned trust root with the same
#      malicious-co-mutation vector.
#
# All other paths are intentionally unowned — no default CODEOWNERS behavior
# is introduced elsewhere in the repo by this file.

/.review/** @pdavis
/agent/vendor/pi/VERSION @pdavis
/agent/vendor/pi/CHECKSUMS @pdavis
/agent/vendor/nvm/VERSION @pdavis
/agent/vendor/nvm/CHECKSUMS @pdavis
/agent/vendor/gh/VERSION @pdavis
/agent/vendor/gh/CHECKSUMS @pdavis
/agent/vendor/yq/VERSION @pdavis
/agent/vendor/yq/CHECKSUMS @pdavis
/agent/vendor/shellcheck/VERSION @pdavis
/agent/vendor/shellcheck/CHECKSUMS @pdavis
/agent/vendor/gitleaks/VERSION @pdavis
/agent/vendor/gitleaks/CHECKSUMS @pdavis
